column4: <content>Jan Brueghel. Sale Mrs. S. van Berg, Sotheby's 25-6-1969. Jan Brueghel the Elder & Hendrick van Balen. 87. 'Raphael's Dream' signed and dated 1595, on metal. Based on an engraving of 1565 by Giorgio Ghisi of 1561. Repr. in Catal. If the date is correct, this would be during Jan B's  Stay in Italy. How does the H. van Balen come in?</content>
